name: The Flats at Northside
description:
ABOUT THE HOME ENERGY RATING SCALE
The HERS (Home Energy Rating System) Index allows buyers to compare the relative energy efficiency of different homes. The HERS Index home energy rating is determined by an independent RESNET-certified home energy rater ("Rater"). The lower a home’s score, the more energy efficient it is in comparison to the HERS referenced home. For every one-point decrease in the HERS Index score, there is a corresponding one percent (1%) reduction in energy consumption as compared to a home with a HERS Index of 100. A home with a HERS score of 100 reflects a home built to 2006 IEEC Building Codes. See the bottom of this page for more information on HERS scores.

amenities.name: Walk LifeTime
amenities.description: Walk to LifeTime Fitness or head to nearby Kennedy Shriver Aquatic Center

amenities.name: Flats Northside
amenities.description: The Flats at Northside keeps you close to the outdoors! Head to Potomac Woods Park, Fall Road Park, Cabin John Regional Park, Beverly Farms Local Park, and Tilden Woods Local Park.

amenities.name: Nearby Watts
amenities.description: Nearby is Watts Branch Stream Valley Park, Woodland Trail, Civic Center Croyden Creek Trail and Nature Center, Lake Bernard Frank and more!

amenities.name: Walk Park
amenities.description: Walk to Park Potomac, home to MoCo's Founding Farmers, Pama Thai, Gringos & Mariachis, King Street Oyster Bar & more.

amenities.name: Closeby Clyde's
amenities.description: Closeby is Clyde's Tower Oaks Lodge. Or simply pick up your own ingredients at Whole Foods.

amenities.name: Closeby Park
amenities.description: Closeby to Park Potomac is Potomac Community Recreation Center, Montgomery County Recreation and Elmwood Smith Community Center.
